# MockMate 🎯

*A Django-based learning platform for practice problems, quizzes, video-based courses, and AI-powered mock interviews.*

## 📌 Status

🚧 **In Development** — This project is actively being built.
Some modules are functional, while others are under construction.

---

## 📖 Overview

MockMate is an advanced online learning platform designed to help students practice coding, test their knowledge through quizzes, learn from video-based lessons, and prepare for interviews with AI assistance.
It takes inspiration from platforms like **GeeksforGeeks** & **Coursera**, but with unique features like adaptive learning, personalized progress tracking, and social post sharing.

---

## 🚀 Current Features (Implemented)

* **User Roles** — Learner, Tutor, Admin.
* **Course Module** — Video-based lessons with progress tracking.
* **Quiz Module** — Linked to courses with certificate generation.
* **Practice Problems** — Live code execution via JDoodle API.
* **Tutor Dashboard** — Add/edit/delete content, bulk CSV import.
* **Social Posts** — Users can create posts, like, comment, repost.
* **Smart Search** — Detects whether you are searching for users, courses, or posts.
* **Light/Dark Theme** — Manual CSS theme switcher.

---

## 🛠️ Planned Features (To Be Added)

* Adaptive learning based on user performance.
* Real-time contests.
* Gamification (badges, leaderboards).
* AI-enhanced code analysis.
* Enhanced analytics for tutors.
* Mobile-friendly responsive UI.

---

## 📂 Project Structure

```
mockmate/
│── core/           # Global features & search
│── courses/        # Courses & video lessons
│── quizzes/        # Quizzes & certificates
│── practice/       # Practice problems & code execution
│── tutor/          # Tutor dashboard & CSV uploads
│── posts/          # Social feed & interactions
│── templates/      # HTML templates
│── static/         # CSS, JS, images
│── manage.py       # Django management script
```

---

## ⚙️ Tech Stack

* **Backend**: Django, Python
* **Frontend**: HTML, CSS, JavaScript (with manual dark mode)
* **Database**: SQLite (dev), PostgreSQL (planned)
* **APIs**: JDoodle for code execution
* **Version Control**: Git & GitHub

---

## 📦 Installation

```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/mockmate.git
cd mockmate

# Create virtual environment
python -m venv myenv
source myenv/bin/activate  # (Linux/Mac)
myenv\Scripts\activate     # (Windows)

# Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

# Run migrations
python manage.py migrate

# Start development server
python manage.py runserver
```

